WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.351
<i>- Previously on
"Superman & Lois"...</i>

00:03.394 --> 00:05.222
- Your mom wanted us
to move to Smallville

00:05.266 --> 00:06.615
- This family
needs Smallville.

00:06.658 --> 00:08.051
<i>- About a year ago,</i>

00:08.095 --> 00:09.357
I took a bunch
of my mom's pills.

00:09.400 --> 00:11.011
She made a really big
drama out of it.

00:11.054 --> 00:12.751
Lots of therapy.

00:14.188 --> 00:15.580
- Hey!
That's my girlfriend!

00:15.624 --> 00:17.147
- Girlfriend? <i>
- It is an article</i>

00:17.191 --> 00:19.323
<i>I am working on
about Morgan Edge.</i>

00:19.367 --> 00:21.760
He's not here
to save Smallville.

00:21.804 --> 00:23.023
<i>Edge changed my story.</i>

00:23.066 --> 00:24.502
I can't let him do this.

00:24.546 --> 00:26.852
That is the best writing
I have done

00:26.896 --> 00:29.029
since you took over.

00:29.072 --> 00:30.769
<i>I already quit.</i>

00:30.813 --> 00:33.076
- When can you start?
- So I can go to school?

00:33.120 --> 00:35.296
- We have to keep an eye
on your powers.

00:35.339 --> 00:39.082
- His photonucleic effect
appears to be insignificant.

00:39.126 --> 00:42.564
He will never be like you,
Kal-El.

00:46.568 --> 00:50.659
<i>♪</i>

00:50.702 --> 00:52.748
- Does this have
too much blue in it?

00:54.315 --> 00:55.751
- I still like
the Huntsman's Tribute.

00:57.405 --> 00:59.407
- Dad, I'm pretty sure
that's just slang for "poop."

00:59.450 --> 01:01.061
- Hey.
- Jonathan.

01:01.104 --> 01:02.366
Don't be gross.

01:02.410 --> 01:04.716
Also, he's not wrong.

01:04.760 --> 01:06.544
- Mom, can we just
pick something?

01:06.588 --> 01:08.329
- Sweetie, this is
an important decision.

01:08.372 --> 01:10.461
We're finally putting our own
stamp on this house.

01:10.505 --> 01:12.550
- If you'd make up your mind.

01:12.594 --> 01:19.383
<i>♪</i>

01:19.427 --> 01:20.993
- What about this color?

01:21.037 --> 01:22.604
You like this color?

01:22.647 --> 01:23.735
- Yeah, it's fine.

01:23.779 --> 01:25.085
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

01:25.128 --> 01:27.043
<i>♪</i>

01:27.087 --> 01:29.089
- Ah!
- Someone is just asking

01:29.132 --> 01:31.743
for the Huntsman's Tribute.
- Anything but Dad's color!

01:31.787 --> 01:33.136
- Oh, come on!

01:33.180 --> 01:34.964
Oh.
You really want to do this?

01:35.007 --> 01:37.271
- No super tricks.
All right?

01:37.314 --> 01:38.489
- Come on.
Come on.

01:38.533 --> 01:40.056
You have to do
better than that!

01:40.100 --> 01:41.710
<i>♪</i>

01:43.755 --> 01:46.236
- Okay, you're done.
That's it, that's it!

01:49.283 --> 01:52.068
<i>♪</i>

01:53.330 --> 01:55.941
<i>♪</i>

01:55.985 --> 01:58.553
<i>- Clark?
Clark?</i>

02:02.296 --> 02:03.601
Guess there's no reason
to hide it

02:03.645 --> 02:05.777
now that you both know
he's Superman.

02:05.821 --> 02:07.605
<i>♪</i>

02:14.221 --> 02:18.834
<i>♪</i>

02:20.879 --> 02:23.273
<i>♪</i>

02:24.840 --> 02:26.015
<i>♪</i>

02:28.844 --> 02:34.850
<i>♪</i>

02:43.032 --> 02:44.860
- Oh!

02:44.903 --> 02:49.995
<i>♪</i>

02:53.173 --> 02:58.874
<i>♪</i>

03:05.097 --> 03:10.102
<i>♪</i>

03:16.544 --> 03:18.241
<i>- Wait, so you can hear</i>

03:18.285 --> 03:20.765
every sound
in the world at once?

03:20.809 --> 03:23.246
- It's more like I hear all
the fluctuations taking place

03:23.290 --> 03:25.379
in the collective
sonic frequency.

03:25.422 --> 03:27.337
- That makes zero sense to me.

03:27.381 --> 03:29.513
- So how do you tell
between, like,

03:29.557 --> 03:31.515
someone in trouble and someone
shouting for a taxi?

03:31.559 --> 03:33.474
- Well, it took lots of years
of training

03:33.517 --> 03:35.040
at the Fortress,
but that's where I learned

03:35.084 --> 03:37.521
to hone in on certain sounds,
like people in distress.

03:37.565 --> 03:39.175
- Wait, be for real, though.

03:39.219 --> 03:41.264
What's the most embarrassing
thing you've ever heard?

03:41.308 --> 03:42.787
- Nope.
Not appropriate.

03:42.831 --> 03:45.312
- Be honest.
Was there nudity involved?

03:45.355 --> 03:46.748
- Maybe when you guys
are older.

03:46.791 --> 03:48.489
- Oh, come on, come on!
- What?

03:48.532 --> 03:50.317
- Another time, another time.

03:50.360 --> 03:51.883
- I would've much rather had
super hearing

03:51.927 --> 03:53.929
than crazy-ass laser eyes.
- Hey, let's just stick

03:53.972 --> 03:55.887
with calling
it "heat vision" for now, okay?

03:55.931 --> 03:58.325
- Mm-hmm.
- And don't be so sure.

03:58.368 --> 04:00.283
Every power comes
with its own burden.

04:00.327 --> 04:01.806
- And responsibilities.

04:01.850 --> 04:02.851
- You mean rules.

04:02.894 --> 04:04.679
- Which are meant
to protect you.

04:04.722 --> 04:06.724
- Yeah.
"Don't use my powers,

04:06.768 --> 04:09.205
don't draw attention
to myself."

04:09.249 --> 04:10.815
- Oh, "Don't feed him
after midnight."

04:10.859 --> 04:12.904
- Hey, it's important
that we don't draw

04:12.948 --> 04:14.906
unnecessary attention
to our family.

04:14.950 --> 04:16.995
If anyone ever found out
the truth about me,

04:17.039 --> 04:18.954
it would change everything.

04:18.997 --> 04:20.303
- It's not like
we're worried you two

04:20.347 --> 04:21.739
are gonna post it on Facebook.

04:21.783 --> 04:24.089
- I mean, yeah,
we're not soccer moms.

04:24.133 --> 04:26.918
- My point is, you need to be
mindful of your actions.

04:26.962 --> 04:29.181
It's the small things
that'll raise suspicion.

04:29.225 --> 04:31.401
- Look, when I was your age,
my dad was really strict,

04:31.445 --> 04:33.490
and at the time,
it seemed unfair.

04:33.534 --> 04:36.798
But now, I realize it gave me
a normal life.

04:36.841 --> 04:38.756
And that's what I want
for the two of you.

04:38.800 --> 04:41.629
- Yeah, if by "normal" you mean
we're cast out like lepers,

04:41.672 --> 04:43.892
Smallville High has it covered.

04:43.935 --> 04:46.547
- All I'm asking
is that you're careful, okay?

04:46.590 --> 04:48.070
I can't always be there.

04:50.159 --> 04:52.857
- Okay.
- Yeah, all right.

04:56.818 --> 04:58.776
- Couldn't we just sat
in the waiting room?

04:58.820 --> 05:00.952
- What if somebody
we know came in?

05:00.996 --> 05:02.693
They might ask questions.
- You know,

05:02.737 --> 05:04.391
if this is something
you're so embarrassed about,

05:04.434 --> 05:06.393
then maybe we shouldn't
be doing it anymore.

05:06.436 --> 05:09.918
- We agreed, Kyle.
This is important.

05:09.961 --> 05:11.311
- It's been a year, Lana.

05:11.354 --> 05:12.877
- Why does it feel like

05:12.921 --> 05:14.488
I'm the only one that's still
worried about this?

05:14.531 --> 05:15.967
- Will you stop
with this again?

05:16.011 --> 05:17.621
You're not the only one
worried about this.

05:17.665 --> 05:20.015
- You sure have a funny way
of showing it.

05:20.058 --> 05:21.843
Hey, honey.

05:21.886 --> 05:23.801
- Hey, <i>mija.</i>

05:23.845 --> 05:26.326
- How did it go
with Dr. Lawrence?

05:26.369 --> 05:28.153
- That's...between me and her.

05:28.197 --> 05:31.156
- I just want to make sure
you're doing okay, that's all.

05:32.201 --> 05:35.465
- Then stop asking me about it
every 10 seconds.

05:35.509 --> 05:37.162
-
- I'm seeing Dr. Lawrence

05:37.206 --> 05:39.077
like you asked, okay?

05:40.209 --> 05:43.343
Can we just go now?
Dad?

05:44.387 --> 05:45.997
- Roger that.

05:51.655 --> 05:53.091
<i>- Hey, you weren't
in first period class</i>

05:53.135 --> 05:55.137
this morning.
Everything all right?

05:55.180 --> 05:57.661
- Not according to my mom.

05:57.705 --> 06:01.361
It's fine, it's just some dumb
family drama stuff.

06:01.404 --> 06:03.188
- Hey, uh--

06:03.232 --> 06:04.625
I've been meaning
to ask you this.

06:04.668 --> 06:07.541
After school,
could we possibly hang out--

06:07.584 --> 06:09.238
- Oh, I--I'm gonna be late,

06:09.281 --> 06:11.588
so I'll talk to you later?

06:13.416 --> 06:16.071
- Close, but no cigar, pal.

06:16.114 --> 06:17.855
Nice try.

06:26.124 --> 06:31.129
<i>♪</i>

06:43.272 --> 06:46.536
<i>♪</i>

07:06.643 --> 07:11.169
<i>♪</i>

07:12.475 --> 07:13.911
- Hey, short stack...

07:13.955 --> 07:15.870
<i>♪</i>

07:15.913 --> 07:17.437
Why is it every time I see you,

07:17.480 --> 07:18.699
you're flirting
with my girlfriend?

07:18.742 --> 07:20.483
- Look, I don't know what
you're talking--

07:20.527 --> 07:24.487
<i>♪</i>

07:24.531 --> 07:26.097
<i>Hey!
What are you doing?</i>

07:26.141 --> 07:27.577
<i>- First, you kiss Sarah,
and now I catch you</i>

07:27.621 --> 07:29.536
slobbering all over like a--
- Hey!

07:29.579 --> 07:31.189
Get away from him!

07:31.973 --> 07:33.931
What are you doing? Come on.
- Thank you.

07:33.975 --> 07:35.193
<i>♪</i>

07:35.237 --> 07:36.934
<i>- Jordan. Come on.
- Thank you.</i>

07:36.978 --> 07:38.936
- Hey!
- Don't you walk away from me.

07:38.980 --> 07:42.113
<i>- Jordan, Jordan, Jordan--</i>

07:42.157 --> 07:44.594
Jordan, Jordan!

07:44.638 --> 07:47.336
<i>- Look at him, he's shaking.</i>

07:47.379 --> 07:48.946
- Jordan!

07:48.990 --> 07:51.122
<i>♪</i>

07:51.166 --> 07:52.210
<i>- Oh, this is pathetic.</i>

07:52.254 --> 07:53.777
- Hey, guys!

07:55.344 --> 07:57.128
Wow, this place has...

07:57.172 --> 07:59.174
- Whatever.
- Really not changed

07:59.217 --> 08:01.132
since I went here.

08:04.788 --> 08:06.660
- I didn't need your help.

08:07.312 --> 08:09.358
- Apparently needed Dad's.

08:09.401 --> 08:10.620
What are you doing here?

08:10.664 --> 08:12.100
- Oh, just wanted to, you know,

08:12.143 --> 08:14.015
see how things were going
at your new school.

08:14.058 --> 08:15.799
- So you decide
to randomly drop by

08:15.843 --> 08:17.540
during fifth period?

08:17.584 --> 08:19.368
- This wasn't random.

08:19.411 --> 08:21.501
He was spying on us.

08:21.544 --> 08:23.546
- What?

08:26.593 --> 08:30.771
<i>♪</i>

08:30.814 --> 08:33.208
- I was just making sure
that you were okay.

08:33.251 --> 08:34.949
- Yeah, you could've said
something this morning,

08:34.992 --> 08:36.690
but instead,
you lied to our faces.

08:36.733 --> 08:39.475
- It wasn't a lie.
You just didn't ask.

08:39.519 --> 08:40.737
- How long have you
been doing this?

08:40.781 --> 08:42.391
Since we moved here?
Our whole lives?

08:42.434 --> 08:44.088
- It's not like I'm listening
all the time.

08:44.132 --> 08:46.874
- That is--that is
the wrong answer.

08:49.180 --> 08:50.530
- You know, I thought
you said it was okay

08:50.573 --> 08:51.835
for me to go to school.
- It is.

08:51.879 --> 08:53.533
- Yes.
- Jordan, having a new power

08:53.576 --> 08:54.751
is a lot.
- Yeah.

08:54.795 --> 08:56.405
So that was a lie too.

08:56.448 --> 08:58.581
<i>♪</i>

09:00.235 --> 09:02.106
- Oy.

09:08.069 --> 09:12.073
-
- So how was your first day?

09:12.116 --> 09:14.249
- I tried following up
on those reverse mortgages,

09:14.292 --> 09:16.033
but it turns out,
people aren't interested

09:16.077 --> 09:18.862
in talking to someone
not from Smallville.

09:18.906 --> 09:20.864
- Well, trust takes time.

09:20.908 --> 09:23.737
People around here,
they'll warm up soon enough.

09:23.780 --> 09:26.478
- You spoken to the boys
since earlier?

09:26.522 --> 09:29.394
- Nope.
Radio silence.

09:29.438 --> 09:31.179
- Do you remember
the first time I caught you

09:31.222 --> 09:33.485
listening in on me?

09:33.529 --> 09:35.618
- How could I forget?

09:35.662 --> 09:38.360
Thought I was gonna
lose you forever.

09:38.403 --> 09:40.101
- You almost did.

09:41.624 --> 09:44.018
- Pretty sure I spent about
a weeks' salary on flowers

09:44.061 --> 09:45.933
just to get you
to talk to me again.

09:45.976 --> 09:48.326
- It was two,
and you got off easy

09:48.370 --> 09:50.764
because I was still
madly in love with you.

09:52.243 --> 09:54.202
- Mm-hmm.

09:54.245 --> 09:55.682
Well...

09:55.725 --> 09:57.292
any suggestions
on how to make things right

09:57.335 --> 09:59.729
with the boys?

09:59.773 --> 10:02.776
- Make them the same promise
you made me.

10:05.648 --> 10:10.087
<i>♪</i>

10:12.176 --> 10:14.439
<i>♪</i>

10:14.483 --> 10:16.398
- You both were right.

10:16.441 --> 10:18.008
I'm sorry.

10:18.052 --> 10:20.271
No more listening in
on your conversations.

10:20.315 --> 10:21.969
I give you my word.

10:22.796 --> 10:25.276
- Mom mentioned something
about flowers.

10:25.320 --> 10:28.279
What are the chances of you
raising my allowance?

10:29.498 --> 10:30.673
Nice try.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.414
We good?

10:32.457 --> 10:34.546
<i>♪</i>

10:34.590 --> 10:36.113
- Sure, whatever.

10:36.157 --> 10:41.510
<i>♪</i>

10:41.553 --> 10:43.643
- How would you like to
interview the keynote speaker

10:43.686 --> 10:45.993
at this year's
Harvest Festival?

10:46.036 --> 10:48.909
- Not sure puff pieces
are really my brand.

10:48.952 --> 10:51.128
- Well, around here,
they sell papers.

10:51.172 --> 10:52.869
I'm afraid not everything
you write for me

10:52.913 --> 10:55.306
is gonna change the world.

10:57.004 --> 10:58.701
- This the paper that just
published that article

10:58.745 --> 11:00.268
about Edge Intercorp?

11:00.311 --> 11:02.705
- Yes, along with a great piece
on birdwatching

11:02.749 --> 11:04.968
and a pretty tricky
crossword puzzle.

11:05.012 --> 11:06.578
- Eh, it wasn't that tricky.

11:06.622 --> 11:08.668
Now, which one of you is
calling around New Carthage

11:08.711 --> 11:11.758
looking for a new story?

11:11.801 --> 11:14.151
- That would be me.
Miss...

11:14.195 --> 11:16.632
- Powell.
Sharon Powell.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.155
- Miss Powell, I'm Lois Lane.

11:18.199 --> 11:20.592
Does this have anything to do
with Morgan Edge?

11:20.636 --> 11:22.159
- Yeah, you're damn right
it does.

11:22.203 --> 11:24.509
I'm hoping you can help me nail
that bastard's ass

11:24.553 --> 11:25.902
to the wall.

11:28.949 --> 11:30.994
<i>♪</i>

11:31.038 --> 11:35.520
My son was a miner at the
Edge Facility in New Carthage.

11:35.564 --> 11:37.087
Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

11:37.871 --> 11:40.743
- He worked there six months.

11:40.787 --> 11:42.136
Made good money, too.

11:42.179 --> 11:44.225
He even sent some of it
back home.

11:45.269 --> 11:47.010
But that all changed
the day Morgan Edge

11:47.054 --> 11:49.839
offered him "the opportunity
of a lifetime."

11:49.883 --> 11:51.928
- What kind of opportunity?

11:51.972 --> 11:53.408
- I was never too clear
on that.

11:53.451 --> 11:56.367
Derek had to sign
a bunch of paperwork.

11:56.411 --> 11:58.195
Keeping him quiet.

11:58.239 --> 12:01.068
- And why do you think there
was foul play involved?

12:07.901 --> 12:10.338
<i>- Hey, Mom,
wish I caught you.</i>

12:10.381 --> 12:13.297
<i>This opportunity
isn't what I thought it was.</i>

12:13.341 --> 12:15.865
<i>Not sure what's gonna happen,
so...</i>

12:15.909 --> 12:18.128
<i>just wanted you to know
that I loved you.</i>

12:18.172 --> 12:19.564
<i>Bye.</i>

12:19.608 --> 12:21.523
- That was the last time I...

12:21.566 --> 12:23.830
ever heard his voice.

12:23.873 --> 12:25.701
- I'm sorry.

12:28.748 --> 12:31.794
<i>♪</i>

12:31.838 --> 12:33.753
- Thank you.

12:37.713 --> 12:43.414
<i>♪</i>

12:46.461 --> 12:48.593
<i>♪</i>

12:48.637 --> 12:50.726
- You can't just
break up with me.

12:50.770 --> 12:53.816
- Have you not been
paying attention?

12:53.860 --> 12:55.992
- Come on.
- Don't.

12:59.430 --> 13:02.303
- Better learn
to stay in your lane.

13:06.829 --> 13:10.267
- One, two, three, four, five.

13:10.311 --> 13:11.268
Seven, eight.

13:11.312 --> 13:14.750
One, two, three, four, five.

13:14.794 --> 13:15.838
Seven, eight.

13:15.882 --> 13:18.928
One, two, three, four, five.

13:18.972 --> 13:21.365
Seven, eight.

13:21.409 --> 13:22.932
What is with the timing?

13:22.976 --> 13:24.455
Sarah!
- What?

13:24.499 --> 13:26.806
- 14 other girls
are working their butts off,

13:26.849 --> 13:28.503
and you're barely
paying attention.

13:28.546 --> 13:29.809
What's going on?

13:29.852 --> 13:31.114
- Relax, Mom.

13:31.158 --> 13:33.073
- Don't tell me to relax.

13:33.116 --> 13:34.291
This is important.

13:34.335 --> 13:36.380
What has gotten
into you lately?

13:37.904 --> 13:39.557
- You know what, Mom?

13:39.601 --> 13:40.863
I quit.

13:40.907 --> 13:43.648
How about that?

13:43.692 --> 13:46.390
- Sarah, get back here.

13:46.434 --> 13:48.131
Sarah!

13:49.698 --> 13:51.482
- Get 'em, boys.

13:51.526 --> 13:53.484
Come on, boys.

13:53.528 --> 13:55.747
Get your heads into it,
let's go!

13:55.791 --> 13:58.098
Pick up that knee!
Let's go!

13:58.141 --> 14:00.317
- Uh, Kent.
Is that your brother?

14:00.361 --> 14:02.363
- Come on, let's go, people!

14:02.406 --> 14:04.713
Two hands on that ball!
- Hey, Pee-Wee!

14:04.756 --> 14:06.367
Practice is on Saturday!

14:06.410 --> 14:08.238
- He's a walking Disney movie
in cleats.

14:08.282 --> 14:10.153
- Hey, hey, hey.
Hey, dude.

14:10.197 --> 14:11.981
What are you doing?

14:12.025 --> 14:14.157
- Trying out for the team.
- That is a--

14:14.201 --> 14:17.160
a terrible idea
on so many levels, I can't--

14:17.204 --> 14:18.988
- Since when did you become
such a pessimist?

14:19.032 --> 14:21.295
- I don't know, probably since
I saw you in pads.

14:21.338 --> 14:23.732
Jordan, what about your powers?

14:23.775 --> 14:26.300
- I'll go easy.
All right?

14:26.343 --> 14:28.519
- Do you even know
how to do that?

14:28.563 --> 14:29.999
- Don't worry.

14:30.043 --> 14:32.219
Now, who wants to play
some football?

14:32.262 --> 14:34.090
- In the middle.
In the middle, 13, let's go!

14:34.134 --> 14:36.701
- Jordan, that literally
goes against everything

14:36.745 --> 14:38.268
that we talked about with Dad.

14:38.312 --> 14:39.704
- You play for the team
all the time.

14:39.748 --> 14:41.097
What's the difference
if I give it a try?

14:41.141 --> 14:43.491
- Are you being serious?

14:43.534 --> 14:44.884
What is this even about,
Jordan?

14:44.927 --> 14:46.276
You hate sports.

14:46.320 --> 14:47.843
- These guys think
they can push us around.

14:47.887 --> 14:49.453
Well, guess what?

14:49.497 --> 14:51.325
I'm pushing back.

14:51.368 --> 14:53.631
- Let's go, drive that through.
Drive, drive, drive,

14:53.675 --> 14:54.719
drive, drive!

14:54.763 --> 14:56.721
Come on, let's go, people!

14:56.765 --> 14:57.940
All right.

14:57.984 --> 14:59.202
When you came by earlier,
I thought

14:59.246 --> 15:01.726
the other coaches
was pranking me.

15:01.770 --> 15:03.728
But here you are.

15:03.772 --> 15:05.034
All right.

15:06.253 --> 15:08.037
Simon!

15:08.081 --> 15:10.083
Go on, take some reps
at corner.

15:10.779 --> 15:12.085
Go on.
- Yes, Coach!

15:12.128 --> 15:13.651
Thank you, Coach!

15:13.695 --> 15:15.305
- It's not a military drill,
Jordan.

15:15.349 --> 15:17.960
- You're gonna need to put
that helmet on.

15:18.004 --> 15:19.657
Let's go, people!
Let's go!

15:19.701 --> 15:20.920
Come on, now!
Let's go!

15:20.963 --> 15:22.486
Pick up the pace!

15:22.530 --> 15:26.403
- Red Eighty,
Red Eighty.

15:26.447 --> 15:28.014
Set, hut!

15:29.667 --> 15:31.408
<i>♪</i>

15:36.196 --> 15:37.588
- This is my lane now, bro.

15:37.632 --> 15:40.591
<i>- ♪ Ooh, la, la,
ah, oui, oui ♪</i>

15:40.635 --> 15:42.854
<i>♪ Ooh, la, la</i>

15:42.898 --> 15:44.813
<i>♪ Lookin' for M's
like I lost a friend ♪</i>

15:44.856 --> 15:46.684
<i>♪ Jump out of my bed like,
"Where the bread?" ♪</i>

15:46.728 --> 15:48.686
<i>♪ You gon' hold the egg,
waiter bring the check ♪</i>

15:48.730 --> 15:50.471
<i>♪ When we talk,
we Kalashnikov ♪</i>

15:50.514 --> 15:52.342
<i>♪ Keep us in your thoughts,
fully dressed ♪</i>

15:52.386 --> 15:55.737
<i>♪ At the crack of dawn,
letting, letting off ♪</i>

15:55.780 --> 15:57.608
<i>♪</i>

15:57.652 --> 16:06.052
<i>♪ Ooh, la, la,
ah, oui, oui ♪</i>

16:06.095 --> 16:07.967
<i>♪ Ooh, la, la</i>

16:08.010 --> 16:09.185
- Whoo!

16:09.229 --> 16:11.971
<i>♪</i>

16:12.014 --> 16:13.059
<i>- ♪ Ah, oui</i>

16:13.102 --> 16:14.451
<i>♪ Ah, oui</i>

16:14.495 --> 16:16.149
Ohh!

16:16.192 --> 16:17.802
<i>- ♪ Ah, oui, oui, oui, oui</i>

16:19.065 --> 16:21.023
- That's what
I'm talking about!

16:21.067 --> 16:22.633
- Thanks, Coach.
- Whoo!

16:22.677 --> 16:23.808
Thank you.

16:23.852 --> 16:26.768
Thank you!
Uh!

16:26.811 --> 16:28.161
Ah, ah!

16:28.204 --> 16:30.511
Hey, where are you going,
QB number two?

16:30.554 --> 16:32.165
Not so fast.

16:32.208 --> 16:33.644
- Excuse me, Coach?

16:33.688 --> 16:35.429
- You got the big cheese,
Ronnie Lott,

16:35.472 --> 16:38.171
for a little brother and you
didn't say nothing to me?

16:38.214 --> 16:40.434
Someone's running today,
smartass.

16:40.477 --> 16:42.914
You give me five
for keeping that from me.

16:42.958 --> 16:44.655
Yeah, go on!

16:46.222 --> 16:49.008
- Pick up the pace,
or I'll put five on it!

16:54.230 --> 16:57.146
<i>- ♪ Do you know your needs?</i>

16:59.061 --> 17:05.024
<i>♪</i>

17:05.067 --> 17:06.155
- So when did you turn into

17:06.199 --> 17:09.506
Mr. All-American
football player?

17:09.550 --> 17:11.421
- I've been practicing
in the backyard with Jon.

17:11.465 --> 17:14.729
- Oh, yeah, yeah.
For sure, every day.

17:16.122 --> 17:18.211
- You two are very
unusual people.

17:20.169 --> 17:22.215
- So I kinda heard
you and Sean earlier.

17:24.434 --> 17:27.524
- It was long overdue.
He's just...

17:27.568 --> 17:30.701
everything I'm not looking for.

17:30.745 --> 17:32.181
- I'm sorry.

17:32.225 --> 17:34.531
- So you--you broke up
with Sean then?

17:34.575 --> 17:36.577
- Well, aren't you
super perceptive.

17:36.620 --> 17:39.188
- So that's why you walked off
the cheer squad earlier?

17:39.232 --> 17:40.929
- Uh, maybe.

17:40.972 --> 17:43.279
We've been in school for, what?
Exactly, like, a week?

17:43.323 --> 17:45.803
And it feels the exact same.

17:45.847 --> 17:47.849
Have you guys ever just wanted

17:47.892 --> 17:51.070
to change your...everything?

17:51.113 --> 17:52.680
- Yeah.
- Not until I moved here.

17:55.117 --> 17:58.990
<i>♪</i>

17:59.034 --> 18:02.646
Uh, Sarah, your mom's coming
in at, like, an EF4 right now.

18:03.517 --> 18:06.476
- Hi, boys.
- Hi, Mrs. Cushing.

18:06.520 --> 18:09.523
- Sarah, can I talk to you
for a minute?

18:09.566 --> 18:12.395
- Whatever you wanna say,
you can say it right here.

18:13.570 --> 18:17.139
- Do you wanna explain to me
what happened back there?

18:17.183 --> 18:19.402
- Isn't it obvious?
I quit the team.

18:19.446 --> 18:21.274
- Mm-hmm, you don't need
to give me attitude.

18:21.317 --> 18:24.103
- Well, you don't have to hover
every single day.

18:24.146 --> 18:25.930
- Look, I'm just trying
to keep you safe.

18:25.974 --> 18:28.237
- Because you think
I'm gonna kill myself?

18:28.281 --> 18:30.239
- Okay, this is not
the appropriate place

18:30.283 --> 18:31.806
to be having this conversation.

18:31.849 --> 18:35.592
- How many times do I have
to tell you I'm fine?

18:35.636 --> 18:37.768
Can't you just trust that
and back off?

18:37.812 --> 18:40.423
- I know you're not telling me
everything that happened.

18:40.467 --> 18:42.730
-
That's hilarious,

18:42.773 --> 18:44.645
coming from the most
full-of-crap lady

18:44.688 --> 18:46.560
in all of Smallville.
- Okay, Sarah--

18:46.603 --> 18:49.128
- No, you act like our family's
so awesome

18:49.171 --> 18:51.826
when it's literally
a dumpster fire.

18:51.869 --> 18:52.957
- Enough.
- Dad sleeps

18:53.001 --> 18:54.394
on the couch every night.

18:54.437 --> 18:56.265
Sophie bullies all of the kids
in her class,

18:56.309 --> 18:59.007
and you can't go to bed
without taking a pill.

18:59.050 --> 19:00.748
- I said that's enough!

19:02.358 --> 19:04.621
Look, grab your stuff.
Let's go.

19:05.448 --> 19:07.755
Now!
-

19:10.236 --> 19:13.326
<i>♪</i>

19:13.369 --> 19:16.503
- Lana?
- Not now, Clark.

19:17.547 --> 19:19.854
- Everything okay with Lana?

19:20.855 --> 19:22.204
- Not really.

19:22.248 --> 19:24.641
- Yeah, she just went all
scorched earth on Sarah.

19:24.685 --> 19:25.947
- Oh.

19:25.990 --> 19:28.732
Well, your mom's working late,
so it's just us.

19:28.776 --> 19:30.778
Anything exciting happen
in school today?

19:30.821 --> 19:32.997
- Actually, football practice
was pretty interesting.

19:33.041 --> 19:34.564
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

19:34.608 --> 19:36.610
Jonathan got a couple
good reps in.

19:36.653 --> 19:38.481
I really think Coach
is starting to take notice.

19:38.525 --> 19:40.353
- Yeah, there's just a little
more to it than that, but--

19:40.396 --> 19:41.963
- That's great!
Let's, uh--

19:42.006 --> 19:45.836
oh, let's celebrate with
some chili cheese fries.

19:48.274 --> 19:49.927
<i>♪</i>

19:49.971 --> 19:53.366
- I think Sharon Powell might
have given us our big break.

19:53.409 --> 19:56.978
- Or--and here's
another theory,

19:57.021 --> 19:58.806
that lady was half in the bag,

19:58.849 --> 20:01.243
selling a conspiracy theory
about her son.

20:01.287 --> 20:02.505
Did you smell her breath?

20:02.549 --> 20:04.638
- I am aware
she'd been drinking.

20:04.681 --> 20:06.857
- I looked into Derek Powell
while you were with his mom.

20:06.901 --> 20:09.469
It turns out, the guy has
a pretty checkered past.

20:09.512 --> 20:11.035
- Even if that's true,
that voicemail

20:11.079 --> 20:12.385
was really compelling.

20:12.428 --> 20:14.561
- Out of context, sure,
but he never once

20:14.604 --> 20:15.997
mentioned Morgan Edge.

20:16.040 --> 20:17.694
Maybe it was just
a drug deal gone wrong.

20:17.738 --> 20:19.479
- That is a stretch.
- But a bazillionaire

20:19.522 --> 20:21.655
making the guy disappear isn't?

20:21.698 --> 20:24.005
- At least give me the chance
to prove I'm right.

20:24.048 --> 20:26.442
- Look, this isn't
the "Daily Planet."

20:26.486 --> 20:29.140
We don't have the resources
to run an investigation

20:29.184 --> 20:30.620
for weeks on end.
- But you hired me

20:30.664 --> 20:32.666
to write this kind of story.

20:41.283 --> 20:46.245
<i>♪</i>

20:49.422 --> 20:51.554
- I hate to ask,

20:51.598 --> 20:53.687
but you don't happen to drive
a station wagon

20:53.730 --> 20:56.864
that's on fire right now...

20:56.907 --> 20:58.822
do you?

21:04.219 --> 21:07.788
- We got the scene cleaned up.
Button up, all right?

21:07.831 --> 21:09.746
I'm sorry about your car, Lois.

21:09.790 --> 21:11.966
- Morgan Edge
was behind this, Kyle.

21:12.009 --> 21:13.533
- Now, hold on,
you shouldn't go around

21:13.576 --> 21:15.317
making baseless accusations
like that.

21:15.361 --> 21:17.232
- It's not baseless.
We just finished talking

21:17.276 --> 21:18.625
to a source about him.

21:18.668 --> 21:21.105
- We still haven't verified
those claims.

21:23.630 --> 21:25.284
- Y'all have a good night.

21:25.327 --> 21:27.938
<i>♪</i>

21:35.642 --> 21:36.947
- Yo, give it back!
- Hey, hey.

21:36.991 --> 21:38.558
Why'd you lie to Dad?

21:38.601 --> 21:41.125
- Why are you whispering?
- I'm--I'm not whispering.

21:41.169 --> 21:43.693
- And I didn't lie to him.
I'm following his example.

21:43.737 --> 21:45.695
- Okay, well, now that you've
made your stupid point,

21:45.739 --> 21:48.089
you're done playing football,
right?

21:49.351 --> 21:50.744
- No, the team needs me.
And besides,

21:50.787 --> 21:52.354
Coach Gaines may even
send me a valentine.

21:52.398 --> 21:54.356
- Jordan, football is my thing,
not yours.

21:54.400 --> 21:56.402
- You don't own football,
you egomaniac.

21:56.445 --> 21:57.881
- The only reason
that you're even playing

21:57.925 --> 21:59.492
is 'cause you have your little
super strength

21:59.535 --> 22:01.145
or whatever.
- The only reason I'm playing

22:01.189 --> 22:04.453
is 'cause your little football
buddies need to back off.

22:04.497 --> 22:05.976
You're welcome.

22:06.020 --> 22:07.543
And besides,
I don't have super strength.

22:07.587 --> 22:08.936
I'm just a little stronger
than before.

22:08.979 --> 22:12.635
- Stop.
What if someone gets hurt?

22:12.679 --> 22:14.289
- You know, I'm getting
a little tired of everyone

22:14.333 --> 22:16.465
treating me like I'm some sort
of ticking time bomb.

22:17.684 --> 22:19.338
You know Dad's gonna find out.

22:19.381 --> 22:20.643
- So what?

22:20.687 --> 22:23.472
I'm not doing anything wrong.

22:23.516 --> 22:26.475
- Guess you got
nothing to worry about then.

22:29.522 --> 22:35.789
<i>♪</i>

22:37.138 --> 22:39.140
- Thought you could use this.

22:43.840 --> 22:45.538
- I made a total fool of myself

22:45.581 --> 22:47.235
accusing Edge like that.

22:48.236 --> 22:50.630
- It's an honest mistake.
- We have been here for a week,

22:50.673 --> 22:52.675
and somebody's already tried
to blow up my car.

22:52.719 --> 22:55.156
-
Look, folks in Smallville,

22:55.199 --> 22:56.853
they're good people.

22:56.897 --> 22:59.073
Don't let what happened today
change that.

22:59.116 --> 23:02.381
Besides, it's not like it's
your first Molotov cocktail.

23:03.251 --> 23:07.429
- I just feel like everyone
here has their walls up.

23:07.473 --> 23:09.213
Maybe I should just
hand the story off

23:09.257 --> 23:10.693
and mend some fences.

23:10.737 --> 23:12.129
- Well, what's your gut
telling you?

23:12.173 --> 23:13.435
- That there's more to this.

23:13.479 --> 23:15.655
- Then you have to dig deeper.

23:15.698 --> 23:18.614
Listen.

23:18.658 --> 23:21.661
I will support whatever
decision you make.

23:22.488 --> 23:25.229
I just want you to be able
to live with it.

23:25.273 --> 23:26.883
- I love you.

23:26.927 --> 23:29.625
- Still?

23:29.669 --> 23:32.236
- Thanks for the flowers.

23:35.283 --> 23:40.288
<i>♪</i>

23:45.598 --> 23:49.384
- Hey.
- Paperwork is all signed.

23:49.428 --> 23:51.038
- Ah, great.

23:51.081 --> 23:53.693
Listen, Clark.
About yesterday--

23:53.736 --> 23:55.912
- Oh, no.
No need to apologize.

23:55.956 --> 23:58.306
- It's just, Sarah quit cheer
out of nowhere

23:58.349 --> 24:02.049
and I suddenly feel like my
whole family is falling apart.

24:04.312 --> 24:05.705
Can you walk?
- Uh, yeah--

24:05.748 --> 24:07.489
oh, I left my keys in the--
it's Smallville.

24:07.533 --> 24:08.969
-
"It's Smallville."

24:09.012 --> 24:10.753
- Uh, and I doubt that,
by the way.

24:10.797 --> 24:12.189
- Well, of course you do.

24:12.233 --> 24:14.322
I mean, that's the image
I've worked so hard

24:14.365 --> 24:16.063
to put out there.

24:16.106 --> 24:17.456
And the truth is,

24:17.499 --> 24:18.935
Kyle and I barely talk.

24:18.979 --> 24:21.242
When we do,
we're yelling at each other.

24:21.285 --> 24:23.505
And Sophie--oh, God, well,

24:23.549 --> 24:25.986
Sophie's just become mean,
and Sarah,

24:26.029 --> 24:29.119
I just feel like
I'm losing Sarah.

24:29.163 --> 24:31.774
- Oh, don't be so sure.

24:31.818 --> 24:34.211
Really hard to know what
they're thinking at this age.

24:34.255 --> 24:36.083
- Oh, God.

24:36.126 --> 24:37.867
Part of me wants to know,

24:37.911 --> 24:40.435
and the other part of me
is terrified

24:40.479 --> 24:42.524
at what I might find out.

24:42.568 --> 24:43.743
- Yeah.

24:43.786 --> 24:45.135
I miss having Mom around
to help

24:45.179 --> 24:46.354
with this sort of thing.

24:46.397 --> 24:47.703
- She would be so happy

24:47.747 --> 24:49.966
to know you're finally home.

24:50.010 --> 24:52.926
And at least the boys
are finally settling in.

24:52.969 --> 24:56.495
I hear Jordan's
quite the football star.

24:56.538 --> 24:58.192
- Oh, I think
you mean Jonathan.

24:59.585 --> 25:00.847
- N-no.

25:00.890 --> 25:02.370
- It's time to get
locked and loaded!

25:02.413 --> 25:03.763
Let's go!
You ready?

25:03.806 --> 25:05.634
It's where the rubber
meets the road.

25:05.678 --> 25:08.637
You ready?
Sean, you're up!

25:08.681 --> 25:10.204
Who do you want?

25:11.422 --> 25:13.424
- I want short-stack, Coach.

25:13.468 --> 25:15.514
- Short-stack!

25:15.557 --> 25:17.341
All right.
Ooh!

25:20.040 --> 25:22.912
- Time to lock horns,
gentlemen.

25:23.609 --> 25:25.045
You ready?

25:26.133 --> 25:27.177
You ready?

25:33.227 --> 25:34.489
<i>♪</i>

25:34.533 --> 25:36.012
Ohh!

25:36.056 --> 25:38.101
- That's what
I'm talking about!

25:38.145 --> 25:40.364
- Whoo!

25:42.628 --> 25:44.760
- I shouldn't
have kissed Sarah.

25:44.804 --> 25:46.588
It wasn't cool.

25:46.632 --> 25:48.242
I apologize.

25:48.285 --> 25:54.335
<i>♪</i>

25:54.378 --> 25:56.032
- All right.

25:58.426 --> 25:59.819
- Yeah.
Thanks.

25:59.862 --> 26:02.386
- Team that plays together
stays together.

26:04.258 --> 26:06.695
All right, who's next up?

26:06.739 --> 26:13.354
<i>♪</i>

26:18.141 --> 26:19.708
- How could you possibly think
it was okay to join

26:19.752 --> 26:21.449
the football team?
- You didn't say it wasn't.

26:21.492 --> 26:23.320
- No, no, don't--don't do that.
I see what you're doing.

26:23.364 --> 26:24.887
- As long as you don't mention
it, it's not a lie, right?

26:24.931 --> 26:26.933
- Your father apologized
for that.

26:26.976 --> 26:29.631
- Your powers are not something
to be taken lightly, Jordan.

26:29.675 --> 26:31.415
- Yeah, well, I barely
have any, remember?

26:31.459 --> 26:33.896
That's what Grand Pabbie told
us at Elsa's Ice Castle.

26:33.940 --> 26:35.463
- That's not funny.
- He was only comparing

26:35.506 --> 26:38.205
your powers to mine.
- No, he said my powers suck.

26:38.248 --> 26:39.859
Don't act like he didn't.
- I admit,

26:39.902 --> 26:42.165
taking you to see him
this early was a mistake.

26:42.209 --> 26:44.080
- Mistake?

26:44.124 --> 26:48.824
You know what?
Everything you do is a mistake.

26:48.868 --> 26:52.001
You get fired,
you bring us here.

26:52.045 --> 26:53.612
You know, I just wish
you would go back

26:53.655 --> 26:55.657
to not being around anymore.

26:57.877 --> 26:59.748
<i>♪</i>

26:59.792 --> 27:01.532
- Go upstairs.
- Yeah.

27:01.576 --> 27:04.448
- Right now.
- Yeah.

27:04.492 --> 27:10.759
<i>♪</i>

27:10.803 --> 27:12.674
- I-I'm with you guys.

27:12.718 --> 27:14.415
I don't know
what he was thinking.

27:14.458 --> 27:16.678
- You too.

27:16.722 --> 27:21.727
<i>♪</i>

27:25.078 --> 27:28.081
- Mm.
Come on, boys.

27:28.124 --> 27:29.082
- Sarah?

27:36.089 --> 27:37.699
Would you please sit down
and have dinner

27:37.743 --> 27:40.354
with the rest of us?
- Nope.

27:40.397 --> 27:42.748
<i>♪</i>

27:48.188 --> 27:51.147
<i>♪</i>

27:53.759 --> 27:57.110
<i>♪</i>

27:57.153 --> 27:59.503
- He didn't mean all that.

27:59.547 --> 28:02.071
- You sure?
- He's 14, he was lashing out.

28:02.115 --> 28:04.421
I'm not saying that
that makes it acceptable,

28:04.465 --> 28:06.728
but we can't take everything
he says at face value.

28:06.772 --> 28:09.209
- Then how am I supposed
to know what he needs?

28:09.252 --> 28:11.864
- All I'm saying is,
maybe figure out the reason

28:11.907 --> 28:14.693
behind Jordan's anger
and address that.

28:14.736 --> 28:16.738
<i>♪</i>

28:16.782 --> 28:18.653
- You going somewhere?
- Yeah.

28:18.697 --> 28:20.046
Turns out, Miss Powell's son

28:20.089 --> 28:21.874
isn't the only worker
who's gone missing.

28:21.917 --> 28:24.659
There's three other employees
I can't account for.

28:24.703 --> 28:26.400
- So you were right?
- Looks like it.

28:26.443 --> 28:28.837
We're meeting in New Carthage
to go over it all.

28:28.881 --> 28:30.186
So, um,

28:30.230 --> 28:31.797
I'm gonna need
to borrow your truck.

28:31.840 --> 28:34.974
<i>♪</i>

28:35.017 --> 28:36.540
- You gonna bring it back?

28:36.584 --> 28:38.368
- 50/50.

28:38.412 --> 28:40.414
<i>♪</i>

28:43.460 --> 28:47.029
<i>♪</i>

28:47.073 --> 28:49.075
- You glad Dad found out?

28:49.945 --> 28:51.555
Now you can just go back
to hanging out with Sarah

28:51.599 --> 28:54.820
and listening to El-P remix
Morrissey, or whatever.

28:54.863 --> 28:57.431
- Morrissey's a xenophobic
has-been.

28:57.474 --> 28:59.738
<i>♪</i>

28:59.781 --> 29:01.783
- Well, you hate football,
right?

29:01.827 --> 29:03.393
So who cares?

29:03.437 --> 29:05.221
You don't have
to pretend anymore.

29:05.265 --> 29:07.571
- Yeah.

29:12.794 --> 29:19.235
<i>♪</i>

29:26.677 --> 29:27.766
- You were right.

29:27.809 --> 29:29.768
I-I should've said something.

29:31.030 --> 29:33.554
That's my bad, I know I'm not
a perfect person.

29:35.034 --> 29:38.515
Trust me.
We all make mistakes.

29:38.559 --> 29:40.735
- Yeah, but what if Jordan
joining the team

29:40.779 --> 29:42.476
wasn't a mistake?

29:43.738 --> 29:45.653
- Not sure I see your point.

29:46.306 --> 29:48.743
- Trust me, this--this feels
really weird to say,

29:48.787 --> 29:51.790
but maybe Jordan
needs football.

29:51.833 --> 29:53.182
I mean, he's been
a really messed up kid

29:53.226 --> 29:54.836
for a really long time.

29:54.880 --> 29:56.142
And, I don't know,

29:56.185 --> 29:58.187
what if joining
the team's a good thing?

29:58.231 --> 29:59.754
- I appreciate you sticking up
for your brother--

29:59.798 --> 30:01.364
- No, look,
it's not even like that.

30:01.408 --> 30:04.541
You should've seen him
out there, he's making friends.

30:04.585 --> 30:08.458
He's been happy for the first
time in...forever.

30:12.462 --> 30:14.203
- Jonathan,

30:14.247 --> 30:17.990
there's nothing I want more
than for you guys to be happy,

30:18.033 --> 30:19.861
but we have to be careful.

30:19.905 --> 30:21.863
And him using his strength
like this, it--

30:21.907 --> 30:23.386
it could raise suspicion.

30:23.430 --> 30:25.475
- Yeah, but he doesn't have
super strength like you.

30:25.519 --> 30:27.651
That's what Jor-El Debarge
said, right?

30:27.695 --> 30:29.088
- Just because his strength
isn't like mine

30:29.131 --> 30:30.524
doesn't mean it's not elevated.

30:30.567 --> 30:32.482
- Okay, so maybe that puts him
on the level

30:32.526 --> 30:34.963
of the other kids.

30:35.007 --> 30:37.226
Okay, maybe he's
a little stronger,

30:37.270 --> 30:38.967
but maybe that does
even the playing field

30:39.011 --> 30:40.316
for a kid his size.

30:40.360 --> 30:43.493
- You don't know that.
- Neither do you.

30:43.537 --> 30:46.322
I know that having powers
is a total game changer,

30:46.366 --> 30:49.195
but what's the point of having
something special

30:49.238 --> 30:51.719
if you're not actually
allowed to be special?

30:51.762 --> 30:55.723
<i>♪</i>

31:04.775 --> 31:09.780
<i>♪</i>

31:30.976 --> 31:35.937
<i>♪</i>

31:40.681 --> 31:42.117
- Sharon?

31:42.161 --> 31:48.515
<i>♪</i>

31:48.558 --> 31:50.125
<i>- And we'll find out what joke
made her laugh hardest,</i>

31:50.169 --> 31:53.955
<i>next on
"The Whitty Banter Show."</i>

31:59.656 --> 32:01.571
<i>♪</i>

32:04.618 --> 32:07.273
<i>♪</i>

32:24.986 --> 32:31.079
<i>♪</i>

32:31.123 --> 32:32.994
Ah, that won't help you.

32:33.038 --> 32:34.343
- No, but he will.

32:38.957 --> 32:43.962
<i>♪</i>

32:53.145 --> 32:58.150
<i>♪</i>

33:07.507 --> 33:08.638
- Sharon?

33:08.682 --> 33:09.944
Sharon.

33:09.988 --> 33:15.036
<i>♪</i>

33:18.735 --> 33:22.043
<i>♪</i>

33:22.087 --> 33:23.740
- Sharon, wake up.

33:23.784 --> 33:24.741
Sharon?

33:24.785 --> 33:26.613
Sharon?
Superman!

33:26.656 --> 33:31.661
<i>♪</i>

33:41.193 --> 33:46.198
<i>♪</i>

33:55.903 --> 33:57.165
Superman!

33:59.341 --> 34:00.299
- He's gone.
Are you okay?

34:00.342 --> 34:01.561
- She's barely breathing.

34:01.604 --> 34:02.866
You need to take her
to the hospital.

34:02.910 --> 34:03.867
I'll be fine.

34:05.217 --> 34:09.351
<i>♪</i>

34:16.010 --> 34:17.751
- Come in.

34:17.794 --> 34:21.102
<i>♪</i>

34:21.146 --> 34:23.061
- I heard about Sean.

34:23.844 --> 34:27.413
- Nothing travels faster
than Smallville gossip.

34:27.456 --> 34:29.632
- Honey, I'm here
if you want to talk about it.

34:29.676 --> 34:31.504
- I'm fine.

34:32.418 --> 34:34.681
- I just can't tell anymore.

34:35.899 --> 34:38.163
Ever since last summer,

34:38.206 --> 34:42.080
I have no idea if I might
lose you forever.

34:47.259 --> 34:49.130
I'm okay, Mom.

34:49.174 --> 34:50.871
I promise.

34:52.046 --> 34:55.615
- Just, we used to be so close.

34:57.573 --> 35:00.185
And now, there's this distance.

35:00.228 --> 35:03.927
And when am I gonna know
that you're really okay?

35:03.971 --> 35:05.973
- 'Cause I'll tell you.

35:06.626 --> 35:09.194
I've been telling you the truth
this whole time.

35:09.237 --> 35:12.022
- Not about why it happened.

35:12.066 --> 35:14.416
Honey, you can quit cheer,

35:14.460 --> 35:17.593
and you can keep me at arm's
distance if you want,

35:17.637 --> 35:22.163
but please, I need to know
why it happened.

35:23.338 --> 35:25.732
- I just felt trapped.

35:27.212 --> 35:29.866
By this town,

35:29.910 --> 35:32.434
by this family.

35:33.653 --> 35:35.307
Everything was getting so bad,

35:35.350 --> 35:38.179
and I just never saw
myself escaping.

35:39.006 --> 35:43.010
It's like the only future
that I saw for myself was...

35:43.053 --> 35:45.795
a life that I didn't want.

35:45.839 --> 35:49.408
<i>♪</i>

35:49.451 --> 35:52.280
- You saw yourself
turning into me.

35:52.324 --> 35:54.543
- That's not what I meant.
- No, it's okay.

35:54.587 --> 35:56.763
It's true.

35:56.806 --> 35:59.244
<i>♪</i>

35:59.287 --> 36:01.942
I'm the most full-of-crap lady
in Smallville.

36:04.249 --> 36:06.903
- And most days,
when I'm smiling,

36:06.947 --> 36:09.776
that's not how I feel inside.

36:09.819 --> 36:11.734
<i>♪</i>

36:11.778 --> 36:14.302
I feel lost.

36:14.346 --> 36:16.826
- Why do you pretend?

36:16.870 --> 36:19.220
<i>♪</i>

36:19.264 --> 36:22.832
-
It's how I was raised.

36:22.876 --> 36:25.226
"Always smile
at your neighbor."

36:25.270 --> 36:27.359
"Never let them see

36:27.402 --> 36:30.188
the hurt inside."

36:30.231 --> 36:32.799
- I don't really think
that's healthy.

36:34.453 --> 36:37.151
I think you're right.

36:37.195 --> 36:43.113
<i>♪</i>

36:43.157 --> 36:46.204
Do you know what kind of life
would make you happy?

36:46.247 --> 36:49.424
<i>♪</i>

36:49.468 --> 36:51.426
- I don't know.

36:52.732 --> 36:56.431
I guess I'm...figuring it out.

36:57.389 --> 37:00.218
- Yeah, me too.

37:00.261 --> 37:03.046
Come here.

37:03.090 --> 37:06.006
<i>♪</i>

37:06.049 --> 37:09.009
I love you so much.

37:09.052 --> 37:11.838
<i>♪</i>

37:19.585 --> 37:24.329
- So is creepy lurking
one of your superpowers now?

37:27.419 --> 37:28.594
- Come on.

37:28.637 --> 37:30.857
I wanna show you something.

37:43.086 --> 37:44.784
When I was in ninth grade,

37:44.827 --> 37:46.568
I wanted to try out
for the baseball team,

37:46.612 --> 37:49.658
but my dad didn't let me.

37:49.702 --> 37:52.574
I begged him over and over,
but...

37:52.618 --> 37:55.273
he always said no.

37:55.316 --> 37:57.840
- So you never even tried out?

37:57.884 --> 37:59.233
- I came close.

37:59.277 --> 38:02.149
You know, showed up
at the field and everything.

38:02.192 --> 38:04.107
But...

38:04.151 --> 38:06.675
at the last minute, I realized

38:06.719 --> 38:09.374
one of the main reasons
I wanted to try out

38:09.417 --> 38:11.767
didn't have anything
to do with baseball.

38:11.811 --> 38:13.943
- Was it a girl?

38:13.987 --> 38:15.423
- It's always a girl.

38:18.078 --> 38:21.168
So did you regret not playing?

38:21.211 --> 38:23.301
- Yeah, I did.

38:23.344 --> 38:28.262
It's been over 20 years
and I still think about it.

38:28.306 --> 38:32.222
Which is why I need you
to be very honest with me.

38:33.136 --> 38:36.401
Is playing football something
that you really want?

38:39.360 --> 38:41.362
- To be honest, at first,

38:41.406 --> 38:42.711
I wasn't sure or anything,

38:42.755 --> 38:44.539
but these last couple of days,

38:44.583 --> 38:47.150
they've--they've kind of
just been incredible.

38:47.194 --> 38:48.804
<i>♪</i>

38:48.848 --> 38:51.546
- And you're sure you can keep
your powers under control?

38:51.590 --> 38:53.548
- Yes.
I'm--

38:53.592 --> 38:55.550
<i>♪</i>

38:55.594 --> 38:58.727
I don't know how to explain it,
it's just a feeling.

39:00.033 --> 39:01.600
I guess you would know.

39:02.862 --> 39:04.385
- Yeah.

39:04.429 --> 39:05.865
Yeah, I think I do.

39:05.908 --> 39:07.606
<i>♪</i>

39:07.649 --> 39:10.304
- Wait.
Does this mean I can play?

39:10.348 --> 39:12.001
- It does.
- Really?

39:12.045 --> 39:13.612
- Yes, but...

39:13.655 --> 39:17.050
there's one last thing
we have to talk about.

39:18.617 --> 39:20.880
- You wanna be
an assistant coach?

39:20.923 --> 39:22.751
- I just want to help out.
I don't know if you know this,

39:22.795 --> 39:25.188
but I was actually the team
manager back in high school.

39:25.232 --> 39:27.277
- LinkedIn resume
notwithstanding,

39:27.321 --> 39:28.583
you're a little late.

39:28.627 --> 39:31.630
We've been staffed up
since the summer.

39:32.892 --> 39:34.676
- Well, you see, the thing is,
with both my boys

39:34.720 --> 39:36.722
on the team now, I'd really
just like to find a way

39:36.765 --> 39:38.419
to spend more time with them.

39:38.463 --> 39:39.942
- Take 'em camping.

39:39.986 --> 39:41.291
Rent a canoe.

39:41.335 --> 39:43.163
Make some s'mores.

39:43.206 --> 39:44.817
- Look, I promise,
I won't get in the way.

39:44.860 --> 39:46.340
I'll do whatever job you need.

39:46.384 --> 39:48.647
- Not to mention,
he'll work for free.

39:50.562 --> 39:53.086
- You should've started
with that, Kent.

39:55.784 --> 39:59.222
- Oh.

39:59.266 --> 40:00.920
- Welcome to the team.

40:00.963 --> 40:03.662
Bring that cooler,
meet me on the sidelines.

40:06.534 --> 40:08.188
- Thanks for the assist.

40:08.231 --> 40:10.364
- You sure about this?

40:10.408 --> 40:11.626
- No.

40:11.670 --> 40:13.236
But I've gotta try.

40:13.280 --> 40:14.716
- All right, I gotta run.

40:14.760 --> 40:16.979
See you later, Coach.
-

40:17.023 --> 40:19.460
- So your dad did a 180
on the whole football thing?

40:20.592 --> 40:22.507
- Got a little help from Jon.

40:22.550 --> 40:26.249
- Well, I can neither confirm
nor deny,

40:26.293 --> 40:28.426
but I will say that--

40:28.469 --> 40:30.819
let's just assume
you owe me now.

40:30.863 --> 40:32.952
- Jonathan, you ready?
- Yeah, oh.

40:32.995 --> 40:35.041
See you guys later.
- Bye!

40:36.477 --> 40:38.523
Um, so,

40:38.566 --> 40:41.047
Friday's gonna be
your first game?

40:41.090 --> 40:42.744
- Yeah, um...

40:42.788 --> 40:44.224
you quit the cheer team,
are you still gonna go?

40:46.313 --> 40:48.184
Do you want me to?

40:48.228 --> 40:49.925
- I mean--
- Yeah!

40:49.969 --> 40:51.666
Yeah, that--it--

40:51.710 --> 40:55.278
it might be fun to see
as a bystander.

40:55.322 --> 40:57.672
<i>♪</i>

40:57.716 --> 40:59.544
Your dad seems like
he's really struggling.

40:59.587 --> 41:02.372
- Oh, yeah, Dad's the new
assistant coach.

41:02.416 --> 41:03.591
- Do you need any help,
Mr. Kent?

41:03.635 --> 41:05.114
-
Oh, hey, Sarah.

41:05.158 --> 41:06.289
Oh, I'm great.

41:06.333 --> 41:07.377
Hey, Coach gave me a jacket

41:07.421 --> 41:08.814
and I bought a hat!

41:09.815 --> 41:11.251
- Uh, um...
- I--

41:11.294 --> 41:14.602
- I'll s--
- Have fun at practice, guys.

41:14.646 --> 41:16.517
- See you, Sarah.

41:16.561 --> 41:18.127
<i>♪</i>

41:18.171 --> 41:19.651
- Hey, looks like you guys
are getting along, huh?

41:19.694 --> 41:21.348
- All right, all right,
all right.

41:21.391 --> 41:22.915
Just pretend like you need
my help with this, all right?

41:22.958 --> 41:24.612
- All right, yeah.
I'm really, really--

41:24.656 --> 41:26.571
ow!
Too much, little too big?

41:26.614 --> 41:28.573
- Little too much.
- All right.

41:29.617 --> 41:30.966
<i>♪</i>

41:31.010 --> 41:34.317
- Lois?
I need to apologize to you.

41:34.361 --> 41:36.319
I mean, after what happened
to Sharon Powell last night,

41:36.363 --> 41:37.625
I feel like such an idiot.

41:37.669 --> 41:39.497
- Chrissy--
- No, it's just--

41:39.540 --> 41:42.978
I've never had something like
this fall on my lap before.

41:43.022 --> 41:45.328
Stories this important
don't usually happen

41:45.372 --> 41:46.634
in Smallville.

41:46.678 --> 41:48.984
- But, see,
that's where I was wrong.

41:49.028 --> 41:52.161
Stories like this happen
in small towns everywhere,

41:52.205 --> 41:54.076
and stories
that need to be told,

41:54.120 --> 41:56.296
but they get missed because
there aren't enough reporters

41:56.339 --> 41:58.690
looking for them.

41:59.821 --> 42:02.520
- Come on, let me show you
what I've been working on.

42:05.044 --> 42:06.698
<i>♪</i>

42:06.741 --> 42:08.090
- Where'd you get this?

42:08.134 --> 42:10.615
- From the gas station
near the motel.

42:10.658 --> 42:14.357
This feels big, doesn't it?

42:14.401 --> 42:16.098
- Yeah.

42:16.142 --> 42:18.927
Now it's up to us
to put it all together.

42:18.971 --> 42:21.582
Who are you, and why
is a person with powers

42:21.626 --> 42:23.932
working for Morgan Edge?

42:24.585 --> 42:27.719
- No, Superman
saved Powell's mother.

42:27.762 --> 42:30.635
Well, how's Larr
gonna take care of it?

42:35.814 --> 42:42.603
<i>♪</i>

42:49.218 --> 42:50.393
- It's done.

42:50.437 --> 42:52.526
I'll call the team.

42:52.570 --> 42:58.184
<i>♪</i>
